alse,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82731"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EWhen a baby is born, they depend heavily on passive immunity passed on from their parent via the placenta.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following immunoglobulins is the only class that can cross the placenta?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["IgA","IgM","IgG","IgD","IgE"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgG\u003C/strong\u003E is the only immunoglobulin that can significantly cross the placental barrier to the neonate. This is important when considering the newborn\u0027s immunity. It also forms the basis for immunisation programmes during pregnancy as the parent\u0027s IgG produced after vaccination can be transferred to the fetus and provide them some level of immunity against infectious diseases until their innate immune system is strong enough and they are old enough to receive immunisations themselves.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgA\u003C/strong\u003E plays an important role in immunity on mucous membranes as it is present in secretions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgM\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in the immediate immune response, as seen by common serological testing whereby IgM peaks first and declines with IgG peaking later and remaining positive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgE\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in hypersensitive reactions, particularly type 1 reactions such as allergy/anaphylaxis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgD\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in the activation of B cells.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["IgG is the only immunoglobulin that can cross the placenta.","Passive immunity is crucial for newborns as it provides them with protection against infections until their own immune system matures."],"references":["Patricia Palmeira, Camila Quinello, Ana L\u00facia Silveira-Lessa, Cl\u00e1udia Augusta Zago, Magda Carneiro-Sampaio, \u0022IgG Placental Transfer in Healthy and Pathological Pregnancies\u0022, Journal of Immunology Research, vol. 2012, Article ID 985646, 13 pages, 2012. https://doi.org/10.1155/2012/985646","Chen K, Cerutti A. The function and regulation of immunoglobulin D. Curr Opin Immunol. 2011;23(3):345-352. doi:10.1016/j.coi.2011.01.006. Access at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3109135/."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67866"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2466"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67866","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67866"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-30T21:42:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-30T21:47:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2466"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82731"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0